dia.org/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-8018-1830-3" title="Special:BookSources/0-8018-1830-3"><bdi>0-8018-1830-3</bdi></a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Deceit%2C+Desire+and+the+Novel%3A+Self+and+Other+in+Literary+Structure&amp;rft.place=Baltimore&amp;rft.pub=Johns+Hopkins+University+Press&amp;rft.date=1966&amp;rft.isbn=0-8018-1830-3&amp;rft.aulast=Girard&amp;rft.aufirst=Ren%C3%A9&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARen%C3%A9+Girard" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/>).</li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFGirard1962" class="citation cs2">&#8212;&#8212;&#8212; (1962), <i>Proust: A Collection of Critical Essays</i>, Englewood Cliffs: Prentice Hall</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Proust%3A+A+Collection+of+Critical+Essays&amp;rft.place=Englewood+Cliffs&amp;rft.pub=Prentice+Hall&amp;rft.date=1962&amp;rft.aulast=Girard&amp;rft.aufirst=Ren%C3%A9&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARen%C3%A9+Girard" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/>.</li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFGirard1963" class="citation cs2">&#8212;&#8212;&#8212; (1963), <i>Dostoïevski, du double à l'unité</i> &#91;<i>Dostoievsky, from the double to the unity</i>&#93; (in French), Paris: Plon</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Dosto%C3%AFevski%2C+du+double+%C3%A0+l%27unit%C3%A9&amp;rft.place=Paris&amp;rft.pub=Plon&amp;rft.date=1963&amp;rft.aulast=Girard&amp;rft.aufirst=Ren%C3%A9&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARen%C3%A9+Girard" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/> (English translation: <cite id="CITEREFGirard1997" class="citation cs2">&#8212;&#8212;&#8212; (1997), <i>Resurrection from the Underground: Feodor Dostoevsky</i>, Crossroad</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Resurrection+from+the+Underground%3A+Feodor+Dostoevsky&amp;rft.pub=Crossroad&amp;rft.date=1997&amp;rft.aulast=Girard&amp;rft.aufirst=Ren%C3%A9&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARen%C3%A9+Girard" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/>).</li>
<li>1972. <i lang="fr" title="French language text">La Violence et le Sacré</i>. Paris: Grasset. <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-2-246-00051-8" title="Special:BookSources/978-2-246-00051-8">978-2-246-00051-8</a>. (English translation: <i>Violence and the Sacred</i>. Translated by Patrick Gregory. Baltimore: Johns Hopkins University Press, 1977. <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-8018-2218-1" title="Special:BookSources/0-8018-2218-1">0-8018-2218-1</a>.) The reprint in the <i lang="fr" title="French language text">Pluriel</i> series (1996; <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/2-01-008984-7" title="Special:BookSources/2-01-008984-7">2-01-008984-7</a>) contains a section entitled "<i lang="fr" title="French language text">Critiques et commentaires</i>", which reproduces several reviews of <i lang="fr" title="French language text">La Violence et le Sacré</i>.</li>
<li>1976. <i lang="fr" title="French language text">Critique dans un souterrain</i>. Lausanne: L'Age d'Homme. Reprint 1983, <i lang="fr" title="French language text">Livre de Poche</i>: <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-2-253-03298-4" title="Special:BookSources/978-2-253-03298-4">978-2-253-03298-4</a>. This book contains <i lang="fr" title="French language text">Dostoïevski, du double à l'unité</i> and a number of other essays published between 1963 and 1972.</li>
<li>1978. <i>"To double business bound": Essays on Literature, Mimesis, and Anthropology</i>. Baltimore: Johns Hopkins University Press. <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-8018-2114-1" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-8018-2114-1">978-0-8018-2114-1</a>. This book contains essays from <i lang="fr" title="French language text">Critique dans un souterrain</i> but not those on Dostoyevski.</li>
